<subSubSection id="C306655C3A129C18E493FB08CFBA5BA1" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA336D73A129C18E493FB08CEA45A81" blockId="3.[151,1437,1196,1510]" box="[199,656,1196,1222]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A129C18E493FB08CD555A81" bold="true" box="[199,353,1196,1222]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F30B76473A129C18E533FB08CD865A81" box="[359,434,1196,1222]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">China</collectingCountry>
!, 
<collectingCountry id="F30B76473A129C18E596FB08CE345A81" box="[450,512,1196,1222]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">India</collectingCountry>
?, 
<collectingCountry id="F30B76473A129C18E642FB08CEB15A81" box="[534,645,1196,1222]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
?
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA336D73A129C18E493FB74CFBA5BA1" blockId="3.[151,1437,1196,1510]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A129C18E493FB74CDD45AAD" bold="true" box="[199,480,1232,1258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">Distributional remarks.</emphasis>
The general external morphology of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D543A129C18E720FB75CFD95AAD" box="[884,1005,1232,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camelus">
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A129C18E720FB75CFD95AAD" box="[884,1005,1232,1258]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">B. camelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D543A129C18E075FB75C9AC5AAD" authority="Salini and Roca-Cusachs" authorityName="Salini and Roca-Cusachs" authorityYear="2021" box="[1057,1432,1232,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A129C18E075FB75C84F5AAD" box="[1057,1147,1233,1258]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">B. petrii</emphasis>
Salini and Roca-Cusachs
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A129C18E4C3FB50CCC45B49" bold="true" box="[151,240,1268,1294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25B57BE3A129C18E4C3FB50CCC45B49" box="[151,240,1268,1294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble each other in general external morphology and can lead to erroneous identification unless the fine details of the external morphology and of male genitalia are closely examined. Therefore, the records from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B76473A129C18E137FABCC9A95B75" box="[1379,1437,1304,1330]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F30B76473A129C18E49CFA98CD035B11" box="[200,311,1340,1366]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
probably correspond to the species 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D543A129C18E684FA99C8665B11" authority="Salini and Roca-Cusachs" authorityName="Salini and Roca-Cusachs" authorityYear="2021" box="[720,1106,1340,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A129C18E684FA99CF195B11" box="[720,813,1341,1366]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">B. petrii</emphasis>
Salini and Roca-Cusachs
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25B57BE3A129C18E00AFA98C88D5B11" box="[1118,1209,1340,1366]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A129C18E00AFA98C8805B11" bold="true" box="[1118,1204,1340,1366]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, though the records need verification. This is because an effort to study the post abdominal structures of the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D543A129C18E0B7FAC4C9A95B3D" authorityName=": Rider" authorityYear="2006" box="[1251,1437,1376,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A129C18E0B7FAC4C9A95B3D" box="[1251,1437,1376,1402]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">Brachycerocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
available from those regions was never attempted. It is also evident from the differences pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D4B263A129C18E16EFA20CCD65B85" author="Schaefer, C. W." pageId="3" pageNumber="510" pagination="204" refId="ref12852" refString="Schaefer, C. W. (1997) Brachycerocoris camelus Costa (Hemiptera: Pentatomidae: Podopinae) in India: New country record. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 99 (1), 204." type="journal article" year="1997">Schaefer (1997)</bibRefCitation>
among the specimens collected from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B76473A129C18E6D0FA0CCE8A5B85" box="[644,702,1448,1474]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F30B76473A129C18E6A6FA0CCF015B85" box="[754,821,1448,1474]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">China</collectingCountry>
with respect to the length and height of medial tubercle on pronotum and scutellum and the shape of tubercle between eyes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
